HEADWORD: Diclinic
<hw>Di*clin"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>di-</grk>
= <grk>di`s-</grk> twice + <?/ to incline.]</ety>
<fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Having two of the intersections between
the three axes oblique. See <er>Crystallization</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Diclinous</ent>⟦br⟧
